# SSH whitelist — copy this file to user/ipsets/ssh-list
# File name = IPSet name.  Type: hash:net (supports single IPs and CIDR subnets)
#
# Format:
#   1.2.3.4           — single IP
#   1.2.3.0/24        — subnet (CIDR)
#   1.2.3.4 # comment — inline comment is stripped, IP is used
#   # full-line comment — preserved in generated script for readability

# Office
1.2.3.4

# Home
5.6.7.8

# VPN exit node
10.0.0.0/24 # corporate VPN
